Class VectorListModel<T>

java.lang.Object
  javax.swing.AbstractListModel
      org.wonderly.jini.serviceui.VectorListModel<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, ListModel
public class VectorListModel<T>
extends AbstractListModel

This is an extension of the AbstractListModel that uses a vector, like default list model, but allows direct access to the vect reference so that you can simply do setContents(Vector<T>) to change the model data.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Gregg Wonderly - gregg.wonderly@pobox.com
